ns.","test_description":"Run report generation with one source adapter configured to fail and two to succeed; verify execution completes, report is still produced, failed section includes `data unavailable`, and process does not abort.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness depends on what the summarizer actually produces (faithfulness to key values), which is model-output quality; deterministic stubs would hide hallucination/omission failures. MOCK-HIDE: a mocked summary function would always pass formatting checks while missing real semantic errors. MULTI-STEP: only one model decision is required (summary generation), so Workflow is not the minimum. REJECTION-GATE: rejected Workflow because behavior text is singular: \"The narrative summary accurately represents...\" with no multi-agent or multi-decision chain.","test_description":"Use a fixed dataset with critical numeric/key facts, call the real summary model, and score output for factual inclusion/consistency against those facts (e.g., rubric or extractor-based checks) across repeated runs with acceptance thresholds for faithfulness.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.68,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: this explicitly requires end-to-end delivery to a real inbox, which crosses process/network boundaries; in-process mocks can hide SMTP/API auth, transport, MIME, and inbox-delivery failures. MOCK-HIDE: mocked mail clients can pass while real